LAFIA  – Nasarawa State government said it has earmarked the sum of N N2.23billion out of the 2022 budget for the electri­fication of rural communities across the state. Hon. Daniel Agyeno, the state Commissioner of Fi­nance, Budget and Planning Commission, made the disclo­sure during the budget break­down at the Ministry in Lafia, the state capital. According to him, the 2022 budget tagged ‘Budget of Sustainable Transformation’ was based on the collective purpose to sustain the pace of development in the state. Buhari Inaugurates NNPC Board, Outlines Guidelines For… NIA DG Never Failed Promotion Examination – ONSA The commissioner also explained that the govern­ment also earmarks N2.8bn for construction of Urban, Rural roads. Agyeno noted that the amount set aside for the road construction was captured in the State’s 2022 Budget which was recently signed into law by Governor Abdullahi Sule. He said, “The state gov­ernment will embark on the construction of some urban roads in Obi Local Govern­ment Area, Karu LGA, Keana LGA, Toto LGA, Keffi LGA, Akwanga LGA, Wamba LGA, Doma LGA and Garaku town in Kokona LGA.”